<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,870,1365]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<taxonomicName authority="Efetov &amp; Tarmann, 1999" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Tarmann" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Jordan" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[151,344,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Jordanita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[151,344,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Jordanita graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a xerothermophilous species of Ponto-Mediterranean distribution. It inhabits dry grassy plains or slopes and steppe (
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[441,683,943,969]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[559,609,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al</emphasis>
. 1999
</bibRefCitation>
). It is distributed from central Europe across the Balkan peninsula, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[300,377,979,1005]" name="Russia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Russia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[388,481,979,1005]" name="Ukraine" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
, Transcaucasia, 
<collectingCountry box="[660,741,979,1005]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, all to 
<collectingCountry box="[811,909,979,1005]" name="Armenia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Armenia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[922,1159,979,1005]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[1039,1094,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
). Historical records from 
<collectingCountry box="[198,280,1015,1041]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
are rather scarce (
<bibRefCitation author="Habeler, H." box="[493,652,1015,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="67 - 86" refId="ref9412" refString="Habeler, H. (1976) Beitrag zur Lepidopterenfauna Dalmatiens. Acta entomologica Jugoslavica, 12, 67 - 86." type="journal article" year="1976">Habeler 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Witt, T. J." box="[665,782,1015,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="413 - 440" refId="ref10968" refString="Witt, T. J. (1987) Lepidopterologische Sammelergebnisse der Reisen Franz Daniels nach Istrien in den Jahren 1965 mit 1971 (Lepidoptera, Bombyces et Sphinges). Entomofauna, 8, 413 - 440." type="journal article" year="1987">Witt 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kranjcev, R." box="[796,966,1014,1041]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="200 - 226" refId="ref9746" refString="Kranjcev, R. (1985) Odnos faune makrolepidoptera prema prirodnim i antropogenim stanistima Podravine i podravskih pijesaka (I). Podravski zbornik, 11, 200 - 226." type="journal article" year="1985">Kranjčev 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sasic, M. &amp; Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M." box="[980,1176,1015,1043]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="233 - 248" refId="ref10538" refString="Sasic, M., Nahirnic, A. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. (2016) Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera) in the Lepidoptera collections of the Croatian Natu- ral History Museum. Natura Croatica, 25, 233 - 248. https: // doi. org / 10.20302 / NC. 2016.25.19" type="journal article" year="2016">
Šašić 
<emphasis box="[1048,1107,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Of those, the records of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kranjcev, R." box="[229,414,1050,1077]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="200 - 226" refId="ref9746" refString="Kranjcev, R. (1985) Odnos faune makrolepidoptera prema prirodnim i antropogenim stanistima Podravine i podravskih pijesaka (I). Podravski zbornik, 11, 200 - 226." type="journal article" year="1985">Kranjčev (1985)</bibRefCitation>
from Podravina should be marked as questionable, as in its work, he does not mention the method in which he determined the correct specie’s identification and the record is far apart from other known localities for this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[514,596,1123,1149]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[612,681,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1889,1913]" captionTargetBox="[157,1425,187,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-28@14.[151,1436,181,1865]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution of Jordanita graeca in Croatia based on newly collected data and historical records." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4643403" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4643403/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
). Within this survey the species was recorded at five additional localities, all located in the wider coastal areas of the country. One specimen was recorded also on Korčula island and represents a new species for that island which was not recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rauch, H." box="[997,1154,1195,1221]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="64 - 71" refId="ref10351" refString="Rauch, H. (1981) Ein Beitrag zur Zygaenenfauna der Insel Korcula in Dalmatien (Jugoslawien). Atalanta, 12, 64 - 71." type="journal article" year="1981">Rauch (1981)</bibRefCitation>
. While the species seems to be widely distributed all across coastal parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[752,837,1231,1257]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
, it cannot be regarded as common. Indeed, it has been recorded on karstic habitats, usually grasslands, which are nowadays under threat of succession and disappearance. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Naumann, C. M. &amp; Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G." box="[414,666,1303,1329]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" refId="ref10290" refString="Naumann, C. M., Tarmann, G. M. &amp; Tremewan, W. G. (1999) The western Palaearctic Zygaenidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo, Stenstrup, 304 pp." type="book" year="1999">
Naumann 
<emphasis box="[530,585,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">et al.</emphasis>
(1999)
</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authority="Efetov &amp; Tarmann, 1999" authorityName="Efetov &amp; Tarmann" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Jordan" baseAuthorityYear="1907" box="[673,777,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Jordanita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="graeca">
<emphasis box="[673,777,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">J. graeca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is usually present on dry grassy plains or slopes with rocks or rocky soil, which is the exact description of the habitats in 
<collectingCountry box="[888,974,1339,1365]" name="Croatia" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Croatia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
